section#dialogs
	h2 Dialogs
	p
		button.primary(
			onclick='window.confirmDialog("Are you sure thatâ€™s what you want to do?", function () { alert("You confirmed"); })'
		) Action!
	h3 Usage:
	pre: code
			| window.confirmDialog(msg, fn, danger, verb)
	dl
		dt `msg` (String)
		dd The message to display
		dt `fn` (Function)
		dd The function to execute if the user presses the confirm button
		dt `danger` (Boolean, optional)
		dd If `true`, the button uses the `$errorColour` (which is probably red). The default is `false`, in which case it uses `$primaryColour`
		dt `verb` (String, optional)
		dd The text to display in the confirm button. Default is `Confirm`

